The '''3PX-series protocol droid''' or '''3PX series droids'''<ref name="Complete">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> were third-degree [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droids]] produced by [[Cybot Galactica/Legends|Cybot Galactica]] in [[50 BBY/Legends|50 BBY]] as an extension of the company's [[3PO-series protocol droid/Legends|3PO-series protocol droid]] line.

==History==
The 3PX line was marketed exclusively in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]<ref name="NEGD" />, and due to the diversity of that region, had a less [[Human/Legends|Human]] design than the mainline 3PO units. The 3PX-series could not match the 3PO's popularity, in large part due to its harsh, angular face, similar to that of the later [[RA-7 protocol droid/Legends|RA-7 protocol droid]] model. The series thus enjoyed only a limited production run.

One of the most infamous 3PX units was [[C-3PX]], converted into an [[Assassin droid/Legends|assassin droid]] by [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]]<ref name="EpIAdv">''[[Episode I Adventures 3: The Fury of Darth Maul]]''</ref> and later refitted with the chassis of a 3PO unit by [[Raith Sienar/Legends|Raith Sienar]].<ref name="NEGD" />

[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] used one of these droids, [[K-3PX]], in his search for [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] on [[Gamandar]].<ref name="marvel75" />

==Behind the scenes==
3PX-series protocol droids first appeared with the character K-3PX in the [[Star Wars (1977) 75|75th issue]] of the [[Star Wars (1977)|1977 ''Star Wars'']] series by [[Marvel Comics]],<ref name="marvel75">[[Star Wars (1977) 75|''Star Wars'' (1977) 75]]</ref> written by [[Mary Jo Duffy]] and illustrated by [[Ron Frenz]] and first published on [[June 14]], [[1983]].<ref name="Marvel Age">''[[Marvel Age]]'' #3</ref> Another 3PX-series protocol droid, [[C-3PX]], then later appeared in the [[Droids (1994) 3|third issue]] of [[Star Wars: Droids (1994)|''Star Wars: Droids'' (1994)]] first published on by [[June 21]], [[1994]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].<ref name="Droids-Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54161/star_wars_droids_1994_3|text=Star Wars: Droids (1994) #3}} {{C|First printing}}</ref> He then later reappeared in the junior novel ''[[Episode I Adventures 3: The Fury of Darth Maul]]'' and it's [[Episode I Adventures 3: The Fury of Darth Maul|accompanying Game Book]] written by [[Ryder Windham]] and published in [[November]] [[1999]].<ref name="EpIAdv" />

